<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7262> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7262" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129. The praenomen is M. in the Smyrna copy of the SC de agro Pergameno (see now Sherk, RDGE no. 12, pp. 63-73). The difference in tribe from no. 25, below, suggests that he may be a Lucilius Rufus, perhaps an uncle of the monetalis (MRR 2.444; but see now Crawford, RRC 1.327, no. 324). See A. B. West, AJPh 49, 1928, 240-253. (LRT) On the possibility that the date should be ca. 101, see above, on M'. Aquillius (10). Cos. 129 or M'. Aquillius (11), Cos 101.\n" .
